irobots.vision

Class Camera

  • java.lang.Object
    • irobots.vision.Camera

  • public class Camera
extends java.lang.Object
    Abstracts the access to the NXTCam and provides utility functions to read the objects detected by the camera.

        Returns:
        returns true if at least one object has bee detected. False otherwise

      • robotDetected

        public boolean robotDetected()
        Checks if a robot has been detected by the camera.

        This method returns true when an object has been detected that belongs to one of the colormaps defined for the robots (0,1,2)

      • detectRobot

        public DetectedObject detectRobot(int colormap)

        Attempts to detect the distance and angle to the robot with the given colormap. If the robot is not seen by the camera this method returns null.

        This method just checks a single robot with the given id. In order to check for all robots use detectRobots()

        Parameters:
        colormap - The colormap(=robot id) of the robot to detect.
        Returns:
        The detected robot or null if the robot is not seen by the camera.

      • getNearestId

        public int getNearestId(DetectedObject[] objs)
        This method can be used to find out which of the detected objects is closest to the camera. If the given does not contain any detected objects (the array is empty or all entries are null) this method returns -1.
        Parameters:
        objs - The detected objects for which the closest should be determined.
        Returns:
        The index in the given array of detected objects which belongs to the object which is closes to the camera

      • detectRobots

        public DetectedObject[] detectRobots()

        Checks all robots if they can be detected and returns an array containing the information about the detected robots. The index in the array equals the id of the robot. If a robot is not seen by the camera its entry in the array is null.

      • getObjectAngle

        public static double getObjectAngle(java.awt.Rectangle obj)

        Parameters:
        obj - The object to which the angle should be calculated
        Returns:
        The angle to the given object in degrees.
